/my-garage-door-stops-when-closing";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.networx.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:61:{i:0;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:1;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:2;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:3;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:4;s:63:"My Lift master garage door would just open up late at night an.";i:5;s:94:"This video will show you how I fixed my garage door from opening by itself seemingly randomly.";i:6;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:7;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:8;s:99:"As these wires short against the housing the electrical impulse causes the door opener to activate.";i:9;s:132:"The number two reason for your Garage Door opening randomly is your Garage Door itself or to be more exact the Safety Sensors on it.";i:10;s:132:"All Garage Doors manufactured after 1993 incorporated Safety Sensors which enabled it to sense if the descending door hit an object.";i:11;s:101:"A garage door that randomly opens by itself is not a common problem but does occur from time to time.";i:12;s:161:"Garage door openers operate on one of many frequencies and while it is possible for one of your neighbors remotes to open your garage door it is highly unlikely.";i:13;s:86:"Newer openers operate on rolling codes making it almost impossible for this to happen.";i:14;s:153:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:15;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:16;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:17;s:67:"This infrared sensor 